<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="58" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="58">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="58">
This record is the first of this species in the north of Mexico, but it has been previously collected in the south of Mexico and in the south of USA, and thus is probably distributed across the whole country. Unlike 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Ogcodocera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ogcodocera leucoprocta" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucoprocta">Ogcodocera leucoprocta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Ogcodocera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ogcodocera analis" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">Ogcodocera analis</taxonomicName>
has its most northern distribution in Arizona and Texas.
</paragraph>
